    <h2>Maintaining Your Commercial Roti Machine</h2>
    <p><strong>Daily:</strong> Clean all food-contact surfaces after each use. Remove dough residue from the press and conveyor. Check gas connections for leaks.</p>
    <p><strong>Weekly:</strong> Deep clean the conveyor belt and heating elements. Check belt tension and alignment. Lubricate moving parts as specified by the manufacturer.</p>
    <p><strong>Monthly:</strong> Check electrical connections. Inspect gas burners for even flame distribution. Have a technician check and calibrate cooking temperatures.</p>
    <p>Well-maintained commercial roti machines typically last 8–15 years. Poorly maintained machines may start having problems within 2–3 years.</p>

