        <div class="faq-a">Automatic roti making machine prices in India range from ₹2,50,000 for a basic fully automatic model to ₹8 lakh or more for high-capacity industrial models producing 1,000+ rotis per hour. Semi-automatic machines cost ₹45,000 – ₹2,50,000 depending on capacity and features.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">How many rotis per hour can a commercial machine make? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">Semi-automatic machines produce 300–600 rotis per hour. Fully automatic machines produce 600–2,000+ rotis per hour depending on the model. Industrial machines can produce 3,000+ per hour. For most restaurants and canteens, a machine making 600–800 rotis per hour is sufficient.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Can a roti machine make different types of Indian breads? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
        <div class="faq-a">Most commercial roti machines are designed for standard wheat flour rotis/chapatis. Some models can also make parathas (thicker settings) and jowar/bajra rotis. Very few can make naans (which require tandoor cooking) or phulkas (which need direct flame). Always check the machine's compatibility with your specific requirements before buying.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Where to buy a roti making machine in India? <span class="icon">+</span></button>
